nt-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Xiaomi Mi 10i is powered by a 5G-ready Snapdragon 750G 8nm processed chipset. This is Qualcomm�s midrange 5G mobile platform that delivers 20% more performance than SD730G. The phone runs on the Android 11 operating system based on MIUI skin on top. Also, it has a better combo of 8GB RAM and a compelling Adreno 619 GPU that improves gaming and daily tasks on the phone.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The smartphone gets charged from a 4,820mAh Li-Po battery and ships with a 33W in-box charger. The battery size is ample and based on that it is expected to deliver a full day of juice. This can benefit the buyers who spent more time on the screen.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Storage and Connectivity</span></p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Mi 10i comes with 128GB of UFS 2.2 storage support that improves app/game launch time. Also, you get huge storage for keeping your photos, videos, music, videos, etc. Also, the phone supports memory cards and offers a hybrid card slot.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">On the connectivity side, it has 4G, 5G (in-selected markets), VoLTE for HD clear voice calls, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.1, a 3.5mm headphone jack, and a USB Type-C port for OTG and charging. Live location tracking constellations like GPS with dual-band A-GPS, GLONASS, Galileo, and BDS are present.</p></div>', 'Xiaomi Mi 10i', '<h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 12px 0px 5px 12px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: dashed; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: initial; border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: rgb(191, 206, 222); border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 24px; width: auto; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: normal;\">XIAOMI MI 10I (8GB RAM + 128GB) DETAILS</h3><div class=\"description long-description description-wrapper long-description-wrapper\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 5px 16px 12px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 18px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); position: relative; letter-spacing: normal;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Xiaomi Mi 10i 8GB+128GB variant loaded with a 5G-ready Snapdragon 750G SoC. The phone brings a 6.6-inch FHD+ 120Hz punch-hole display, a 108MP quad-rear camera with dual-LED flash, a 16MP selfie camera, and is backed by a 4,820mAh battery with a 33W fast charger. Let�s get more information about it and see how it performs.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px