powered by a 5G-ready Snapdragon 750G 8nm processed chipset. This is Qualcomm�s midrange 5G mobile platform that delivers 20% more performance than SD730G. The phone runs on the Android 11 operating system based on MIUI skin on top. Also, it has a better combo of 8GB RAM and a compelling Adreno 619 GPU that improves gaming and daily tasks on the phone.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The smartphone gets charged from a 4,820mAh Li-Po battery and ships with a 33W in-box charger. The battery size is ample and based on that it is expected to deliver a full day of juice. This can benefit the buyers who spent more time on the screen.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Storage and Connectivity</span></p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Mi 10i comes with 128GB of UFS 2.2 storage support that improves app/game launch time. Also, you get huge storage for keeping your photos, videos, music, videos, etc. Also, the phone supports memory cards and offers a hybrid card slot.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">On the connectivity side, it has 4G, 5G (in-selected markets), VoLTE for HD clear voice calls, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.1, a 3.5mm headphone jack, and a USB Type-C port for OTG and charging. Live location tracking constellations like GPS with dual-band A-GPS, GLONASS, Galileo, and BDS are present.</p></div>', 'Xiaomi Mi 10i (8GB RAM + 128GB) Specifications', 'Dual Sim, GSM+GSM (Hybrid Slot)', 1, 'Nano', 'Smartphone', 'January 05, 2021', '165.38?x?76.8?x?9?mm', '182 gm', 'Color IPS LCD screen (16M)', '120hz', '1', 'with Multitouch', '6.67?inches, 1080?x?2400?pixels', '20:9', '~395?PPI', '~?84.6%', 'Corning Gorilla Glass 5', 1, 'Punch Hole', 8, '128', 1, '(Hybrid Slot), upto 512?GB', 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'Dual Stand-By', 1, 'with wifi-hotspot', 1, 'v5.1, A2DP, LE', 1, ' USB-C v2.0', 'USB on-the-go, USB Charging', 1, ' with dual-band A-GPS, GLONASS, BDS, GALILEO', 1, 'Side', 1, 'Ultra-sound Proximity Sensor, 360� Ambient Light Sensors, Accelerometer, Gyroscope, Electronic Compass, Z-axis Linear Vibration Motor', 1, '', 1, '108MP f/1.75 (Wide Angle) <br>8MP f/2.2 (Ultra Wide)<br> 2MP f/2.4 (Macro) 2MP f/2.4 (Depth Sensor) with autofocus', 'HDR , AI Scene Detection, Night Mode 2.0, Panorama, Pro Mode, Raw mode, Portrait Mode', 1, '4K?@?30fps UHD, 1080p?@?30/60fps FHD, 720p?@?30fps HD', 1, 'Yes, Dual LED', 1, 'Punch Hole 16?MP f/2.45 (Wide Angle)', 1, '1080p?@?30fps FHD, 720p?@?120fps HD', 'Android v10, upgradable to v11', 'Qualcomm Snapdragon 750G', '2.2?GHz, Octa Core Processor', '2x2.2 GHz Kryo 570 & 6x1.8 GHz Kryo 570', 'Adreno 619', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'MP3, FLAC, APE, AAC, OGG, WAV, WMA', 1, 'MP4,MKV,AVI,WMV,WEBM,3GP,ASF,MOV,TS', 1, 1, 'Non-Removable Battery', '4820?mAh, Li-Po Battery', 1, '33W Fast Charging', '', '', 0, '2022-04-12 13:11:29'),
(62, 82, 'Samsung Galaxy F23 5G', 'samsung', '16999', 'samsung-galaxy-f23-5g', '16497088901.webp,16497088902.webp,16497088903.webp,16497088904.webp,16497088905.webp,16497088906.webp,16497088907.webp,16497088908.webp', 'samsung', '<p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G is a mid-range smartphone with inciting features onboard. The phone carries a 120Hz FHD+ screen protected with Gorilla Glass 5, a 50MP triple rear & an 8MP front camera, a massive 6,000mAh battery backed by fast charging, a side fingerprint scanner, and is powered by a Snapdragon 750G chipset paired with 4GB RAM and 128GB built-in storage. Read more about the smartphone in detail and see how it stands against its competitor Apple iPhone SE 3.</p><h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 16px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G Display and Camera</h3><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G includes a tall 6.6-inch IPS LCD screen with a waterdrop notch. The phone promises improved visuals with an FHD+ (1080x2408px) display and a pixel density of 401ppi. On top of that, it comes protected with a layer of Gorilla Glass that ensures extra durability.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">The backside of the phone has vertically aligned triple cameras mounted on a rectangular bump. The brand has added a 50MP primary camera followed by an 8MP ultrawide camera, and a 2MP depth sensor with autofocus. Besides, the phone has an 8MP front-facing camera for capturing selfies.</p><h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 16px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G Performance and Battery</h3><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Galaxy F23 5G is a mid-range smartphone powered by a Snapdragon 750G chipset. It is paired with 4GB RAM and an Adreno 619 GPU that boosts its gaming and multitasking performance. As for the software, the phone runs on Android 12-based OneUI 4.1 skin atop.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">This is a mid-range Samsung smartphone loaded with a massive 6,000mAh Li-Ion battery under the hood. On the other hand, the phone ships with a fast 25W charger out of the box that cuts extra time for charging.</p><h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 16px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G Storage and Connectivity</h3><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G comes with 128GB of inbuilt storage capacity. Also, the storage is expandable via an SD card slot that offers more storage for extra files.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">The smartphone�s connectivity options are 5G (in-selected markets) 4G, VoLTE with dual standby, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.0, a USB (v2.0) Type-C port, NFC for contactless payment, and a 3.5mm audio jack. Besides, it has GPS with A-GPS, GLONASS, Galileo, and Beidou for online location tracking</p>', 'Samsung Galaxy F23 5G', '<p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G is a mid-range smartphone with inciting features onboard. The phone carries a 120Hz FHD+ screen protected with Gorilla Glass 5, a 50MP triple rear & an 8MP front camera, a massive 6,000mAh battery backed by fast charging, a side fingerprint scanner, and is powered by a Snapdragon 750G chipset paired with 4GB RAM and 128GB built-in storage. Read more about the smartphone in detail and see how it stands against its competitor Apple iPhone SE 3.</p><h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 16px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G Display and Camera</h3><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G includes a tall 6.6-inch IPS LCD screen with a waterdrop notch. The phone promises improved visuals with an FHD+ (1080x2408px) display and a pixel density of 401ppi. On top of that, it comes protected with a layer of Gorilla Glass that ensures extra durability.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">The backside of the phone has vertically aligned triple cameras mounted on a rectangular bump. The brand has added a 50MP primary camera followed by an 8MP ultrawide camera, and a 2MP depth sensor with autofocus. Besides, the phone has an 8MP front-facing camera for capturing selfies.</p><h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 16px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G Performance and Battery</h3><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Galaxy F23 5G is a mid-range smartphone powered by a Snapdragon 750G chipset. It is paired with 4GB RAM and an Adreno 619 GPU that boosts its gaming and multitasking performance. As for the software, the phone runs on Android 12-based OneUI 4.1 skin atop.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">This is a mid-range Samsung smartphone loaded with a massive 6,000mAh Li-Ion battery under the hood. On the other hand, the phone ships with a fast 25W charger out of the box that cuts extra time for charging.</p><h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 16px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G Storage and Connectivity</h3><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">Samsung Galaxy F23 5G comes with 128GB of inbuilt storage capacity. Also, the storage is expandable via an SD card slot that offers more storage for extra files.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); letter-spacing: normal;\">The smartphone�s connectivity options are 5G (in-selected markets) 4G, VoLTE with dual standby, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.0, a USB (v2.0) Type-C port, NFC for contactless payment, and a 3.5mm audio jack. Besides, it has GPS with A-GPS, GLONASS, Galileo, and Beidou for online location tracking</p>', 'samsung', 'Dual Sim, GSM+GSM', 1, 'Nano', 'Smartphone', 'March 08, 2022', '165.5?x?77?x?8.4?mm', '198?g', 'Color TFT screen (16M)', '120hz', '1', 'with Multitouch', '6.6?inches, 1080?x?2408?pixels', '20:9', '~401?PPI', '~?82.3%', 'Corning Gorilla Glass 5', 1, 'Water Drop Notch', 4, '128', 1, 'upto 1?TB', 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'Dual Stand-By', 1, 'with wifi-hotspot', 1, ' v5.0, A2DP, LE', 1, 'USB-C v2.0', 'USB on-the-go, USB Charging', 1, 'with A-GPS, Glonass, Beidou, Galileo, QZSS', 1, 'Side', 1, 'Accelerometer, Electronic Compass, Gyro Sensor, Geomagnetic Sensor, Virtual Light Sensing, Virtual Proximity Sensing', 1, 'NFC', 1, '50MP f/1.8 (Wide Angle)<br>\r\n8MP f/2.2 (Ultra Wide)<br>\r\n2MP f/2.4 (Depth Sensor) with autofocus', 'AR Zone, Bixby Vision, Food, Hyperlapse, Macro, Night, Panorama, Photo, Portrait, Pro, Pro Video, Scene Optimizer, Single Take, Slow Motion, Super Slow-Mo, Video', 1, '1080p', 1, 'LED', 1, '8?MP f/2.2 (Main)', 1, '1080p?@?30fps FHD', 'Android v12', 'Qualcomm Snapdragon 750G', '2.2?GHz, Octa Core Processor', '2x2.2 GHz Kryo 570 & 6x1.8 GHz Kryo 570', 'Adreno 619', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'MP3, M4A, 3GA, AAC, OGG, OGA, WAV, AMR, AWB, FLAC, MID, MIDI, XMF, MXMF, IMY, RTTTL, RTX, OTA', 1, 'MP4, M4V, 3GP, 3G2, AVI, FLV, MKV, WEBM', 1, 1, 'Non-Removable Battery', '5000?mAh, Li-ion Battery', 1, '25W Fast Charging', '44?hours', '130?hours', 0, '2022-04-12 02:28:10'),
(64, 112, 'Realme 9 Pro 5G', 'Realme', '21990', 'realme-9-pro-5g', '16497459471.webp,16497459472.webp,16497459473.webp,16497459474.webp,16497459475.webp,16497459476.webp', 'Realme 9 Pro 5G ', '<h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 12px 0px 5px 12px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: dashed; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: initial; border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: rgb(191, 206, 222); border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 24px; width: auto; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: normal;\">REALME 9 PRO 5G DETAILS</h3><div class=\"description long-description description-wrapper long-description-wrapper\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 5px 16px 12px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 18px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); position: relative; letter-spacing: normal;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Realme 9 Pro 5G comes as a successor to the�<a href=\"https://www.smartprix.com/mobiles/realme-8-pro-5g-ppd1pt9zpcu3\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: red; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; font-style: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(0, 136, 204);\">Realme 8 Pro</a>�smartphone. In terms of the specs & features, it offers a 6.6-inch FHD+ 120Hz screen, a 64MP triple-rear & a 16MP front camera, a side fingerprint scanner, a big 5,000mAh battery supported by a 33W charger, and the phone is powered by a Snapdragon 695 chipset with 6GB+128GB internal storage. Let�s dive into its details and see how the phone performs against its competitors.</p><h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; font-size: 16px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.3;\">Realme 9 Pro 5G Display and Camera</h3><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Realme 9 Pro 5G is fitted with a 6.6-inch IPS LCD punch-hole display. The phone also has a 120Hz screen for better touch interaction and an FHD+ resolution with a pixel density of 400PPI improves its picture quality.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The smartphone brings a 64MP triple-rear camera setup with an LED flash. It has a primary camera with an aperture of f/1.7, an 8MP ultrawide sensor, and a 2MP macro camera for taking close-up shots. Besides, the phone comes along with a 16MP front camera for assisting selfies and video chats.</p><h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; font-size: 16px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.3;\">Realme 9 Pro 5G Performance and Battery</h3><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Realme 9 Pro 5G runs on the Android v12 operating system with Realme UI 3.0 on top. The smartphone is driven by a Snapdragon 695 octa-core processor embedded on a 6nm chipset. On top of that, it is paired with 6GB RAM and an Adreno 619 GPU for a performance boost. And, the phone features a side-mounted fingerprint scanner and face unlock for security unlocks.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The smartphone retains a big 5,000mAh Li-Po battery under the hood. Also, the phone is backed by a fast 33W charger that offers quick charging and saves time as well. Considering the battery capacity, it might draw the attention of heavy users and gamers who spend more time on screen.</p><h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; font-size: 16px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.3;\">Realme 9 Pro 5G Storage and Connectivity</h3><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Realme 9 Pro 5G comes with 128GB of built-in UFS 2.2 storage that boosts its performance and transferring speed. Also, it has a Hybrid card slot that can be used to keep extra files.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The smartphone has 4G, 5G (in-selected markets), VoLTE with dual standby, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.1, a 3.5mm audio jack, and a USB Type-C port in terms of connectivity preferences. Besides, live location tracing constellations such as GPS with A-GPS, Beidou, and GLONASS are present.</p></div>', 'Realme 9 Pro 5G', '<h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 12px 0px 5px 12px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: dashed; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: initial; border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: rgb(191, 206, 222); border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 24px; width: auto; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: normal;\">REALME 9 PRO 5G DETAILS</h3><div class=\"description long-description description-wrapper long-description-wrapper\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 5px 16px 12px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 18px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); position: relative; letter-spacing: normal;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Realme 9 Pro 5G comes as a successor to the�<a href=\"https://www.smartprix.com/mobiles/realme-8-pro-5g-ppd1pt9zpcu3\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: red; outline-style: initial; outline-width: 0px; font-style: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(0, 136, 204);\">Realme 8 Pro</a>�smartphone. In terms of the specs & features, it offers a 6.6-inch FHD+ 120Hz screen, a 64MP triple-rear & a 16MP front camera, a side fingerprint scanner, a big 5,000mAh battery supported by a 33W charger, and the phone is powered by a Snapdragon 695 chi