(66, 251, 'Xiaomi Mi 10i', 'Xiaomi', '22990', 'xiaomi-mi-10i', '16497474891.webp,16497474892.webp,16497474893.webp,16497474894.webp,16497474895.webp,16497474896.webp', 'Xiaomi Mi 10i (8GB RAM + 128GB) Specifications', '<h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 12px 0px 5px 12px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: dashed; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: initial; border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: rgb(191, 206, 222); border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 24px; width: auto; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: normal;\">XIAOMI MI 10I (8GB RAM + 128GB) DETAILS</h3><div class=\"description long-description description-wrapper long-description-wrapper\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 5px 16px 12px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 18px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); position: relative; letter-spacing: normal;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Xiaomi Mi 10i 8GB+128GB variant loaded with a 5G-ready Snapdragon 750G SoC. The phone brings a 6.6-inch FHD+ 120Hz punch-hole display, a 108MP quad-rear camera with dual-LED flash, a 16MP selfie camera, and is backed by a 4,820mAh battery with a 33W fast charger. Let�s get more information about it and see how it performs.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Display and Camera</span></p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Xiaomi Mi 10i comes fitted with a 6.6-inch IPS LCD screen with a punch-hole design. The display has a Full HD+(1080x2400px) resolution that amounts to a pixel density of 395PPI. Also, it has a full view screen that offers better viewing, plus the display is HDR10 compliant that brings more color details. To prevent scratches, the display is protected with a layer of Gorilla Glass 5.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">For selfies and video calls, the phone includes a 16-MP punch-hole camera. Besides, it carries a highlighted 108MP quad-rear camera setup with dual-tone LED flash. The setup includes the main camera followed by an 8MP ultra-wide sensor and a pair of 2MPs� of a macro camera and a depth sensor with autofocus. Also, the camera app has features such as HDR, AI Scene Detection, Night Mode 2.0, Panorama, Pro Mode, Raw mode, Portrait Mode, etc.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Performance and Battery</span></p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Xiaomi Mi 10i is powered by a 5G-ready Snapdragon 750G 8nm processed chipset. This is Qualcomm�s midrange 5G mobile platform that delivers 20% more performance than SD730G. The phone runs on the Android 11 operating system based on MIUI skin on top. Also, it has a better combo of 8GB RAM and a compelling Adreno 619 GPU that improves gaming and daily tasks on the phone.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The smartphone gets charged from a 4,820mAh Li-Po battery and ships with a 33W in-box charger. The battery size is ample and based on that it is expected to deliver a full day of juice. This can benefit the buyers who spent more time on the screen.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Storage and Connectivity</span></p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Mi 10i comes with 128GB of UFS 2.2 storage support that improves app/game launch time. Also, you get huge storage for keeping your photos, videos, music, videos, etc. Also, the phone supports memory cards and offers a hybrid card slot.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">On the connectivity side, it has 4G, 5G (in-selected markets), VoLTE for HD clear voice calls, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.1, a 3.5mm headphone jack, and a USB Type-C port for OTG and charging. Live location tracking constellations like GPS with dual-band A-GPS, GLONASS, Galileo, and BDS are present.</p></div>', 'Xiaomi Mi 10i', '<h3 style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 12px 0px 5px 12px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: dashed; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: initial; border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: rgb(191, 206, 222); border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 24px; width: auto; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: normal;\">XIAOMI MI 10I (8GB RAM + 128GB) DETAILS</h3><div class=\"description long-description description-wrapper long-description-wrapper\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 5px 16px 12px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Ubuntu, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 18px; overflow: hidden; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); position: relative; letter-spacing: normal;\"><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 14px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Xiaomi Mi 10i 8GB+128GB variant loaded with a 5G-ready Snapdragon 750G SoC. The phone brings a 6.6-inch FHD+ 120Hz punch-hole display, a 108MP quad-rear camera with dual-LED flash, a 16MP selfie camera, and is backed by a 4,820mAh battery with a 33W fast charger. Let�s get more information about it and see how it performs.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Display and Camera</span></p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Xiaomi Mi 10i comes fitted with a 6.6-inch IPS LCD screen with a punch-hole design. The display has a Full HD+(1080x2400px) resolution that amounts to a pixel density of 395PPI. Also, it has a full view screen that offers better viewing, plus the display is HDR10 compliant that brings more color details. To prevent scratches, the display is protected with a layer of Gorilla Glass 5.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">For selfies and video calls, the phone includes a 16-MP punch-hole camera. Besides, it carries a highlighted 108MP quad-rear camera setup with dual-tone LED flash. The setup includes the main camera followed by an 8MP ultra-wide sensor and a pair of 2MPs� of a macro camera and a depth sensor with autofocus. Also, the camera app has features such as HDR, AI Scene Detection, Night Mode 2.0, Panorama, Pro Mode, Raw mode, Portrait Mode, etc.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Performance and Battery</span></p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Xiaomi Mi 10i is powered by a 5G-ready Snapdragon 750G 8nm processed chipset. This is Qualcomm�s midrange 5G mobile platform that delivers 20% more performance than SD730G. The phone runs on the Android 11 operating system based on MIUI skin on top. Also, it has a better combo of 8GB RAM and a compelling Adreno 619 GPU that improves gaming and daily tasks on the phone.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The smartphone gets charged from a 4,820mAh Li-Po battery and ships with a 33W in-box charger. The battery size is ample and based on that it is expected to deliver a full day of juice. This can benefit the buyers who spent more time on the screen.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Storage and Connectivity</span></p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Mi 10i comes with 128GB of UFS 2.2 storage support that improves app/game launch time. Also, you get huge storage for keeping your photos, videos, music, videos, etc. Also, the phone supports memory cards and offers a hybrid card slot.</p><p style=\"margin: 14px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 13px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">On the connectivity side, it has 4G, 5G (in-selected markets), VoLTE for HD clear voice calls, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.1, a 3.5mm headphone jack, and a USB Type-C port for OTG and charging. Live location tracking constellations like GPS with dual-band A-GPS, GLONASS, Galileo, and BDS are present.</p></div>', 'Xiaomi Mi 10i (8GB RAM + 128GB) Specifications', 'Dual Sim, GSM+GSM (Hybrid Slot)', 1, 'Nano', 'Smartphone', 'January 05, 2021', '165.38?x?76.8?x?9?mm', '182 gm', 'Color IPS LCD screen (16M)', '120hz', '1', 'with Multitouch', '6.67?inches, 1080?x?2400?pixels', '20:9', '~395?PPI', '~?84.6%', 'Corning Gorilla Glass 5', 1, 'Punch Hole', 8, '128', 1, '(Hybrid Slot), upto 512?GB', 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'Dual Stand-By', 1, 'with wifi-hotspot', 1, 'v5.1, A2DP, LE', 1, ' USB-C v2.0', 'USB on-the-go, USB Charging', 1, ' with dual-band A-GPS, GLONASS, BDS, GALILEO', 1, 'Side', 1, 'Ultra-sound Proximity Sensor, 360� Ambient Light Sensors, Accelerometer, Gyroscope, Electronic Compass, Z-axis Linear Vibration Motor', 1, '', 1, '108MP f/1.75 (Wide Angle) <br>8MP f/2.2 (Ultra Wide)<br> 2MP f/2.4 (Macro) 2MP f/2.4 (Depth Sensor) with autofocus', 'HDR , AI Scene Detection, Night Mode 2.0, Panorama, Pro Mode, Raw mode, Portrait Mode', 1, '4K?@?30fps UHD, 1080p?@?30/60fps FHD, 720p?@?30fps HD', 1, 'Yes, Dual LED', 1, 'Punch Hole 16?MP f/2.45 (Wide Angle)', 1, '1080p?@?30fps FHD, 720p?@?120fps HD', 'Android v10, upgradable to v11', 'Qualcomm Snapdragon 750G', '2.2?GHz, Octa Core Processor', '2x2.2 GHz Kryo 570 & 6x1.8 GHz Kryo 570', 'Adreno 619', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'MP3, FLAC, APE, AAC, OGG, WAV, WMA', 1, 'MP4,MKV,AVI,WMV,WEBM,3GP,ASF,MOV,TS', 1, 1, 'Non-Removable Battery', '4820?mAh, Li-Po Battery', 1, '33W Fast Charging', '', '', 0, '2022-04-12 13:11:29');

